e scout is just a basic profession!<br>
<br>
This week we are going to do things a little differently. Earlier in the week, Holocron revealed how our profession trees are set up in response to a thread. To help further illustrate this we have decided to release the current flow sheet (ripped from the actual designer’s documents) on one of our starting professions, the Scout.<br>
“Wait a minute,” you are saying, “where did the Scout come from?” During the process of implementing professions we changed the Explorer to the Scout with some modifications to the skill tree. The Scout is a starting profession. Advanced professions, like the Ranger, may require mastery in the Scout profession as a prerequisite.<br>
<br>
For your viewing pleasure, we present the skill tree of the Scout. As you can see, you start by acquiring the Novice title skill. You can then branch out to any of the specializations. To get the Master Title skill though, you must complete all of the specialization skills.<br>
<br>
Unlike most weeks, I’m putting this information directly in the Features section instead of putting it in the FAQ section.<br>
<br>
Also note, this is not the start of us revealing the skill trees for each profession. We just wanted to throw one out there to give you a good idea of how it was done. <br>
<br>
Enjoy <br>
